Mind blowing.

snippet.textDisplay:
Dear Coke Studio,

I would like to express my gratitude for your efforts in showcasing the diverse and rich Sindhi culture, which was previously unfamiliar to many of us. The culture is truly captivating and vibrant, and the language is melodious. The joy and pride reflected on the faces of the people made me feel honored to be a Pakistani.

I am amazed by the exceptional depiction and execution of the folk tale, along with the addictive melody and music. 

Xulfi, it is remarkable how you consistently surpass your own achievements. Thank you once again for this exceptional work

snippet.textDisplay: Being an Indian & truly music enthusiast, I should admit that Pakistan's Coke Studio production is way better than India(Bharat) or Bangla (Bangladesh). Earlier, Strings rocked the show, now it's time for Xulfi. When India & Bangladesh, both are literally struggling & producing average regional tune in Coke Studio but this Pakistan team, headed by Xulfi just nailed every beats. I am not a Sindhi, a pure Bengali but I respect every communities & cultural people. Coke Studio Pakistan depicted the cultural flavour wonderfully. I truly admire their thoughts. Lastly, Peacock entry scene with Musical Peak was awesome. Hats off team, our expectations are too high now. Please bring some more good songs like Pasoori. Thanks
